I"V<p>Given that <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/curse-of-dimensionality-hinders-high-dimensional-mappings">high-dimensional mappings are prone to overfitting</a>, regularization is a term introduced in <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/risk-is-statistical-expectation-of-loss">the training loss</a> to discourage the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/supervised-learning-assumes-underlying-structure">model</a> from employing <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/supervised-learning-is-argmin-in-hypothesis-space-of-model-architecture">many parameters</a>.</p>
